<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100750886532180></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100750886532180><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100750886532180>Our new skills, according to Caster's Realm..</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100750886532180#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=38412><span id=Scholar>Dalantia</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>267 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Dec 4th 6:34 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.42]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Note that we also get the general and archetype-based abilities.&nbsp;&nbsp;eq.castersrealm.com has ALL of the abilities.<br><br>Paladin Class Abilities - 59+<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>2 Hand Bash: (1 skill level - cost 6 skill points) - This ability allows the Paladin to use his Bash skill while wielding any two-handed weapon. (Dal: What we were drooling about.  Not 'til 59. *frown*)<br><br>Act of Valor: (1 skill level - cost 3 skill points) - This ability allows the Paladin to sacrifice his life in order to heal another. The Paladin can use this ability to transfer all of his remaining hit points to a member of his group. This transfer causes the Paladin to die. The Refresh Timer for this ability is 72 minutes (one day of game time). (Dal: I would presume that this wouldn't work after death, but it would be very useful when you NEED to keep the cleric/main tank up and you're the only one with HP.)<br><br>Body and Mind Rejuvenation: (1 skill level - cost 5 skill points - Prerequisite: 3 skill levels of both Melee Archetype abilities Natural Healing and Mental Clarity) - This ability gives the Paladin one additional skill level of both Mental Clarity and Improved Natural Healing. (Dal: 1 HP/MP every six seconds, if I remember correctly)<br><br>Divine Stun: (1 skill level - cost 9 skill points) - This ability gives the Paladin the power to use spells with a stun component to affect NPCs of levels up to 60th. Those spells will still grant the NPC a saving throw and its normal resistances, it only raises the level limitation for stun spells to 60.  (Dal: Ultimate spell stuffers, we have become.)   <br><br>Double Riposte: (3 skill levels) - This ability gives the Paladin a chance for a double riposte any time he successfully ripostes. The first skill level gives the Paladin a 15% chance for a Double Riposte, the second skill level raises that chance to 30% and the third skill level makes the chance 50%.<br><br>Fearless: (1 skill level - cost 6 skill points - Prerequisite: 3 skill levels of the Melee Archetype ability Fear Resistance) - This ability makes the Paladin permanently immune to fear effects.  (Dal: We already have 25% chance to simply resist from the prerequisite Fear Resistance.  If you get it.)<br><br>Holy Steed: (1 skill level - cost 5 skill points) - This ability allows the Paladin to summon the ultimate steed.<br><br>Improved Lay of Hands: (1 skill level - cost 5 skill points) - This ability gives the Paladin the power to heal completely with his Lay on Hands power.  (Dal: Rather than just your natural HP and then some.  Very very nice in the 59-60 range, I'd think.)<br><br>Mass Group Buff: (1 skill level - cost 9 skill points) - This ability gives the Paladin the power to make his next group buff spell into an area of affect spell. The spell would benefit everyone in the area, not just the caster's group. This Ability causes the spell to use up to as much as twice as much mana. It will require at least the normal casting cost, and will use up to as much as twice the mana if the caster has that much available. The Refresh Timer for this ability is 72 minutes (one day of game time).  (Dal: I can't think of any paladins actually wanting this one, but I'm not 59.  One would think that one would use their points on combat skills. *grin*)<br><br>Physical Enhancement: (1 skill level - cost 5 skill points) - This ability gives the Paladin one additional skill level in their Natural Durability, Combat Agility and Combat Stability abilities. (Dal: +2% of all types of AC and HP, assuming you don't have the skill already.)<br><br>Slay Undead: (3 skill levels - Prerequisite: 3 skill levels of the Melee Archetype ability Combat Fury) - This ability turns the Paladin's critical hits into massive damage to undead.  (Dal: Combat Fury = ANY melee crits.  Three levels makes us about equal to warriors.  This = even bigger crits against undead.)<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Dec  4 23:02:04 2001</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Dalantia Dragonet<br>Beloved Cavalier of Catwalkk Silverpaw, 53rd Rank<br>Fennin Ro<br>Second Foundation</td></tr>
