	   <tr><td colspan=2>Jcasetnl,<br><br>I'm sure you are doing nothing wrong.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Lull line of spells are very ineffective.  I use them rarely (read as: Almost never) and with very limited success.  Even my latest and greatest spell "Pacify" it is still very ineffective.<br><br>Keep them in your book (near the back) and use them if you have no other choice. That would be my recommendation.<br><br>I have found they work rather well on Green mobs. Unfortunately, I rarely need the help on Green mobs!<br><br>As for stacking up against the Harmony line of spells that Rangers and Druids receive, there is no comparison in my opinion.  Harmony is a GREAT spell. I spent a lot in my younger days running with a Druid friend of mine. The two of us made and still make a very powerful combination and we have been able to pull off some amazing things that in no small part were due to his use of Harmony.  Our Lull Line of spells aren't even in the same ballpark.<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Cavalier<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
