	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have a level 25 Paladin and I am sad to say that it is my main. But after playing EQ with my Pally me and lots of other people lvl 50+ have come to the conclusion that well...Pallys suck. The only great advantage is Lay Hands Which is usefull once a day. They are good swordsmen and fun to use but once you get to a higher level it starts to get a bit boring. They recieve their healing and other spells like 10 or 20 levels after the real pure casters learn them. The swords they get are great but nowhere close to the swords Rogues and Warriors get. I mean Pallys don't have anything that really makes them stand out. If a group needs a healer get a cleric and if they need a tank there is always a good warrior. The bottom line is groups wouldnt need Paladins for any good reason, there are more useful classes out there.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
