	   <tr><td colspan=2>*shrug*&nbsp;&nbsp;Don't play a class you don't like.<br><br>We're 75% warrior, 25% cleric.  We're not meant to be the main healers.  I've been passed over for warriors and warriors have been passed over for me.  I don't do as much damage as they do, but I can take as much damage as one, especially with my buffs and heals.  There's a reason we call ourselves hybrids.  Because we're not a pure class, we have our own abilities.<br><br>You won't hear anyone demanding a paladin.  Of course, you probably WILL hear about one filling a warrior's spot.  *shrug*  Having a paladin around makes everyone's life easier.  A panic button like LoH can save the group when the cleric calls out of mana, and the paladin can easily taunt a mob off the warrior when things go to heck.  Just because we're a mix doesn't make us weaker, it just makes us different.<br>&nbsp;<br>Dalantia Dragonet<br>Beloved Cavalier of Catwalkk Silverpaw, 53rd Rank<br>Fennin Ro<br>Second Foundation</td></tr>
